    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Because with the current algorithm, the given block would be queried in `get_ancestor(store: Store, root: Hash, slot: Slot)` function recursively.\r\nI had the same question before: https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/1068#discussion_r285386568, but we haven't figured out a better solution yet.\r\n\r\nWe do want to make the fork choice rule spec more abstract in the spec level, however for sanity testing, the `Store` is exposed as status quo. IMO it might need more iterations past spec freeze to make it better.",
